      "beast_baseline": "i get the \"long run\" argument but that's a bit of an easy way out. if we keep waiting for this imaginary \"stable foundation\" while people are literally going broke today, aren't we just prioritizing a balance sheet over human lives? it feels like you're basically saying austerity is the only responsible way to go and any other approach is just \"mistakes.\" isn't that a bit one-sided?",
